cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

This paper proposes a new technique to improve the performance of Generative Adversarial Networks (GAN) by training the self-supervised learning with the adversarial process. The paper focuses on computer vision tasks, specifically image generation, and uses geometric transformations on input images. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper uses adversarial training, which is a common technique in the field of GANs, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper also discusses the use of Auto-Encoder (AE) based-GAN models, which falls under the sub-category of cs.GR (Graphics).
